  • Method Details

    • evaluate

      public abstract void evaluate(String commandText, String[] args, PublicNavigator navigator, PublicLocation topLocation, Writer out)
      Performs the action associated with this command.
      Parameters:
      commandText - The text entered by the user in the QuickJump box.
      args - The arguments entered by the user (i.e., everything after the command, separated by spaces).
      navigator - The Pebbles navigator for the current session.
      topLocation - The top of the Pebbles location stack.
      out - A writer for any miscellaneous output produced by the command.

    • generateSuggestions

      public List<AutocompleteResult> generateSuggestions(String textSoFar)
      Generates a list of autocomplete suggestions based on the text entered by the user.
      Parameters:
      textSoFar - The text entered by the user so far in the QuickJump box.
      Returns:
      A list of AutocompleteResult

    • getDisplayName

      public String getDisplayName()
      Gets the name of this command. This name is displayed in the autocomplete suggestions when the user focuses on the QuickJump box, and must match the first word of the user's input in order for this command to be invoked.

    • checkAgainOnNextKeystroke

      public boolean checkAgainOnNextKeystroke(String textSoFar)
      Returns true if the list of autocomplete suggestions should be refreshed from the server on the user's next keystroke.
      Parameters:
      textSoFar - The text entered by the user so far in the QuickJump box.

    • isPermitted

      public boolean isPermitted()
      Returns true if the current user is permitted to use this command at all.

    • getChainingInputType

      public IType getChainingInputType()
      If this command can be "chained" after another command, returns the type of the output expected from the previous command. Returns null otherwise.

    • setTarget

      public void setTarget(String commandTarget)
      This method is called by the QuickJump configuration parser to handle the "commandTarget" attribute.

    • getTarget

      public String getTarget()
      Returns the "commandTarget" attribute from this command's configuration.

    • setArgs

      public void setArgs(String commandArgs)
      This method is called by the QuickJump configuration parser to handle the "commandArgs" attribute.

    • getKey

      public String getKey()
      Returns a String used to uniquely identify this command, for the purpose of detecting duplicate command definitions. Subclasses should only override this method if two instances of the subclass should be permitted to share a command name - this will only be the case if said instances can be guaranteed never to be available to the user at the same time.

    • setSymbolName

      public void setSymbolName(String symbolName)
      This method is called by the QuickJump configuration parser to handle the "symbolName" attribute.

    • setSymbolType

      public void setSymbolType(String symbolType)
      This method is called by the QuickJump configuration parser to handle the "symbolType" attribute.
